Here’s the flawed event listener code used to capture clipboard events:
javascript
document.addEventListener('copy', async (e) => {
  const copiedText = window.getSelection().toString();
  // Parse timestamps to detect Claude vs user...
});

This failed because `window.getSelection()` only captures text that is currently rendered in the DOM. Since Claude.ai dynamically loads content via virtual scrolling, many AI responses and artifacts exist in JavaScript memory and are not part of the rendered DOM. As a result, the extension missed most of the conversation.
